  "description": [
    "Pare 4 Takes Issue With Conclusions Of Flynn in As We Go Marching Flynn John T As We Go Marching Doubleday Doran Co NY 1944 This book is about fascism in Amer ica So Author Flynn states in this prefatory note There is a sober and pertinent warning too that the end of the war will not mean the end of the fight against fascism here or elsewhere Under these circumstances it is vital that democratic peoples all over the world understand fascism so that it may be identified and stamped out The book is written with just that objective in mind The technique of the writer is simple the style is readable and the conclu sions are definite The better to under stand the threat of fascism its rise and characteristics are traced in both Italy and Germany An analogy with the American scene is then drawn to focus attention on the danger spots in our own civilization SIGNS OF TIMES There is no difficulty in discovering just exactly what these signs of the times are The author lists them for the United States as 1 The institu tion of planned consumption or the spendingborrowing government 2 The planned"
  ],
